You’ll need: Glug of olive oil; 6-8 chicken thighs and drumsticks; salt and milled pepper; ½ coil (150g) chorizo, sliced; 4-5 baby onions, halved; 3-4 garlic cloves, sliced; 2 Tbsp smoked or regular paprika; 2 Tbsp butter; a handful of fresh basil, stalks removed; 2 cups chicken stock; 1 cup fresh cream; 1 can (400g) butter beans, drained; 1 can (400g) red kidney beans, drained; 1 lime How to: Serve with crusty bread, buttery mash or a side salad. *Recipe and image by www.astralchicken.com